{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Character Moral Compass Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook uses Singular Value Decomposition (SVD) on four specific moral traits to visualize character archetypes.\n",
    "\n",
    "### The 4 Moral Traits:\n",
    "1. **Honorable vs. Cunning** (Index 13)\n",
    "2. **Loyal vs. Traitorous** (Index 27)\n",
    "3. **Heroic vs. Villainous** (Index 38)\n",
    "4. **Forgiving vs. Vengeful** (Index 24)\n",
    "\n",
    "Note: In the data, the 'left pole' (Honorable, Loyal, etc.) is represented by negative values and the 'right pole' (Cunning, Traitorous, etc.) by positive values. To make a standard compass where 'Good' is positive, we will flip the signs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set data directory\n",
    "data_dir = 'data/plain/current/2000/'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load data\n",
    "characters_df = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(data_dir, 'data_characters.tsv'), sep='\\t')\n",
    "traits_df = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(data_dir, 'data_traits.tsv'), sep='\\t')\n",
    "A_raw = np.loadtxt(os.path.join(data_dir, 'data_raw_A.txt'))\n",
    "A = A_raw.T # Orientation: (Characters x Traits) -> (2000 x 464)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define Moral Trait Indices\n",
    "moral_indices = [13, 27, 38, 24]\n",
    "moral_traits = traits_df.iloc[moral_indices]['differential'].values\n",
    "\n",
    "# Subset the matrix (and flip signs so positive = Good)\n",
    "A_moral = -A[:, moral_indices]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Subset matrix shape: {A_moral.shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Singular Value Decomposition\n",
    "We decompose the character-trait matrix into $U \\Sigma V^T$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "U, S, Vt = np.linalg.svd(A_moral, full_matrices=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate Principal Components (Character Coordinates)\n",
    "PCs = U * S\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Singular values (S): {S}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Explained variance ratio: {S**2 / np.sum(S**2)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Visualizing the Moral Compass\n",
    "We plot PC1 (the most significant source of variation) vs. PC2."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "plt.axhline(0, color='grey', lw=1)\n",
    "plt.axvline(0, color='grey', lw=1)\n",
    "plt.scatter(PCs[:, 0], PCs[:, 1], alpha=0.3, s=10, c='skyblue', label='All Characters')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Highlight specific characters\n",
    "highlights = [\n",
    "    'Samwise Gamgee',\n",
    "    'The Joker',\n",
    "    'Atticus Finch',\n",
    "    'Lord Voldemort',\n",
    "    'SpongeBob SquarePants'\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "for char_name in highlights:\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        idx = characters_df[characters_df['character'] == char_name].index[0]\n",
    "        plt.scatter(PCs[idx, 0], PCs[idx, 1], color='red', s=50)\n",
    "        plt.annotate(char_name, (PCs[idx, 0], PCs[idx, 1]), xytext=(5, 5), textcoords='offset points')\n",
    "    except IndexError:\n",
    "        print(f\"Warning: Character '{char_name}' not found in characters_df.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Principal Component 1 (Overall Morality)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Principal Component 2 (Secondary Trait Variation)')\n",
    "plt.title('The Moral Compass: SVD on 4 Moral Traits')\n",
    "plt.grid(alpha=0.2)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Interpreting the Dimensions\n",
    "Let's look at $V^T$ to see which traits contribute to which component."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "comp_df = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    Vt,\n",
    "    columns=[t.split(' :: ')[0] for t in moral_traits],\n",
    "    index=[f'PC{i+1}' for i in range(len(S))]\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(\"Principal Component Loadings (Trait weights):\")\n",
    "display(comp_df)"
   ]
  }
 ],
